==Chinese==
===[[Mandarin]]===
*[[Pinyin]]: Jīanhùgōng 

===Noun===
'''[[監]][[護]][[工]]'''

[[caretaker]], [[in-house nurse]]. Note: In Taiwan, the certificate required to be a "in-house nurse" is different from that of a nurse.
===[[Attestation]]===
Laws of Republic of China, Taiwan:

[http://laws.cla.gov.tw/Eng/FLAW/FLAWDAT01.asp?lsid=FL015130 Measures for Employment Permission and Supervision of Foreign Persons]:
:第5條:[ . . . . ]雇主辦理前項求才登記項目為家庭'''監護工'''者[ . . . . ]
:Article 5:[ . . . . ]An employer, who is recruiting for workers to be employed as '''caretakers'''[ . . . . ]

[http://law.moj.gov.tw/Eng/Fnews/FnewsContent.asp?msgid=1173&msgType=en Regulations on the Permission and Administration of the Employment of Foreign Workers]:
: 第12條: [ . . . . ]但申請聘僱外國籍家庭'''看護工'''者 . . . .
: Article 12: [ . . . . ]where an Employer registers to employ '''in-house nurses''' . . . .
